To take the context with your `filterDates` method you need to use arrow functions instead of declaring it as a regular method as you did (otherwise the `this` keyword will be referring to the context inside `matDateFilter` class, where your `pipe` and `apiResult` don&#39;t exist) :

```js
filterDates = (date: Date): boolean =&gt; {
  if (this.apiResult !== undefined) {
    let d = this.pipe.transform(date, &#39;yyyy-MM-dd&#39;);
    return this.apiResult.has(d);
  } else {
    return true;
  }
}
```

