JSON property names and non-numeric values should be in &quot;&quot; (doublequotation mark) instead of &#39;&#39; (sinlequotation mark).

Use another class to wrap collection of JobModel (it&#39;s a good practice but json should be changed too), e.g.:

    class ResultModel
    {
       public ICollection&lt;JobModel&gt; Jobs { get; set; }
    }
    // JSON:
    {
       &quot;Jobs&quot;: [
       {
        // class properties with values
       },
       {
        // class properties with values
       }]
    }

and chang type for deserialize method:

    JsonConvert.DeserializeObject&lt;ResultModel&gt;(data);

If you can&#39;t change JSON then use JArray:

    JArray jJobs = JArray.Parse(json);

and map JObject&#39;s JProperties on your class.

